Not sure this is related to the problem but I noticed this error happening consistently in the cloud-error.log file:
{code}
Fri Mar 6 09:33:40 2015 ERROR [Volumes:Eucalyptus.eucalyptus:EphemeralConfiguration:arn:euca:eucalyptus:::com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.Volumes/.class java.util.concurrent.ThreadPoolExecutor$Worker#434] [com.eucalyptus.blockstorage.Volumes$VolumeUpdateEvent.update(Volumes.java):231] java.util.NoSuchElementException: Failed to lookup ENABLED service of type Storage in partition Partition:name=nested:cc-cert-serial=44963361661160710:nc-cert-serial=44963378329632504
{code}
[~viglesias] mentioned that he removed the nested cluster but something is still referencing it.

This function looks suspect to me: (Component.java)
{code}
593    private void updateBootstrapDependencies( ) {
594      Iterable<Bootstrapper> currBootstrappers = Iterables.concat( Lists.newArrayList( this.bootstrappers.values( ) ),
595                                                                                   Lists.newArrayList( this.disabledBootstrappers.values( ) ) );
596      this.bootstrappers.clear( );
597      this.disabledBootstrappers.clear( );
598      for ( Bootstrapper bootstrapper : currBootstrappers ) {
599        try {
600          Bootstrap.Stage stage = bootstrapper.getBootstrapStage( );
601          if ( bootstrapper.checkLocal( ) && bootstrapper.checkRemote( ) ) {
602            this.enableBootstrapper( stage, bootstrapper );
603          } else {
604            this.disableBootstrapper( stage, bootstrapper );
605          }
606        } catch ( Exception ex ) {
607          LOG.error( ex, ex );
608        }
609      }
610    }
{code}

It isn't thread safe. Assume that you have 1 bootstrapper in this.bootstrappers (which is a synchronizedMultimap) If two threads access it at the same time it is possible for both threads to get the current list of bootstrappers, store it in 'currBootstrappers', line 594. 

Thread A and B would have to hit 596 at roughly the same time, then start iterating over the currBootstrappers iterator. Whichever thread calls line 602 first will cause the other thread to block (since the map.put()) call is synchronized. Then when the second thread enables the bootstrapper, line 602, there will be a duplicate key, so the bootstrapper will get _appended_ to the current value associated with the key (ArrayList of size 1). Now this.bootstrappers has one entry, with the value being an ArrayList of size 2 (2 bootstrappers). 

The second time this happens, the list will be of size 4, 3rd -> 8, 4th -> 16, and so on with exponential growth. This would explain the large ArrayList value in the ArrayListMultimap, along with the large ArrayLists (source is line 594) floating around.
